<p>I am now writing a simple d3 table as follows:</p>  <pre><code>var table_data = [   {Variable: "x", Value: 0},   {Variable: "y", Value: 0} ];  var columns = [   "Variable",   "Value" ];  var table = d3.select("#mytable").append("table"); var thead = table.append("thead"); var tbody = table.append("tbody");  thead.append("tr")   .selectAll("th")   .data(columns)   .enter()   .append("th")   .text(function(column) { return column; });  tbody.selectAll("tr")   .data(table_data)   .enter()   .append("tr")   .selectAll("td")   .data(function(row) {     return columns.map(function(column) {       return {column: column, value: row[column]};     });   })   .enter()   .append("td")   .text(function(d) { return d.value; }); </code></pre>  <p>But I want to update the table when mousemoving. So I add the following codes to my mousemoving function (<code>_x</code> and <code>_y</code> are new pieces of data.):</p>  <pre><code>var mousemove = function() {    // some more irrelevant codes here    var newdata = [{Variable: "x", Value: _x}, {Variable: "y", Value: _y}]    table.selectAll("tbody.tr")     .data(newdata)     .enter()     .append("tr")     .selectAll("td")     .data(function(row) {       return columns.map(function(column) {         return {column: column, value: row[column]};       });     })     .enter()     .append("td")     .text(function(d) { return d.value; }); }; </code></pre>  <p>But when I move the mouse to another data point, one more table is plotted instead of just updating current table with new data. No idea why.</p>  <p>Pls advise! Thanks.</p>